    <blockquote
      cite="mid:5525A3CC-814E-476B-BE7D-5E5FDAE86D33@cisco.com"
      type="cite">
      <pre wrap="">

Here's our numbering scheme:

- In general, an even 2nd number of OMPI's release number indicates a "super stable" series, and an odd number indicates a "feature release" series.  See <a class="moz-txt-link-freetext" href="http://www.open-mpi.org/software/ompi/versions/">http://www.open-mpi.org/software/ompi/versions/</a> for more details.</pre>
    </blockquote>
